<TITLE> Fakhruddin congratulates Zardari </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 7 (bdnews24.com)Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed congratulated newly elected president of Pakistan Asif Ali Zardari on Sunday, the foreign ministry said. "The chief adviser expressed hope that under the leadership of Asif Ali Zardari, Pakistan will move further ahead in peace and harmony," a statement of the ministry said. Fakhruddin also hoped that the existing relations between the two nations will further solidify with president Zardari's assumption of power in Pakistan. He wished the new president health, happiness and peace. bdn
